<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1130,1768]" pageId="9" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,256,1634,1660]" pageId="9" pageNumber="68">Notes</emphasis>
:—Our collection is identical to 
<taxonomicName box="[641,980,1634,1660]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Togniniaceae" genus="Phaeoacremonium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Togniniales" pageId="9" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="croatiense">
<emphasis box="[641,980,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="68">Phaeoacremonium croatiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on morphology and phylogenetic evidence (
<figureCitation box="[252,343,1670,1696]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,190,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[177,1411,190,1915]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogram generated from MP analyses based on a combined dataset of ACT and TUB2 sequence data. Bootstrap support values for ML (back) and MP (red) equal to or greater than 75% are shown above the nodes. The BI values greater than 0.95 are indicated by blue triangle. The new isolates are in blue and ex-type strains are in bold. The tree was rooted with Pleurostoma richardsiae (CBS 270.33)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316486/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="68">FIGS. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[358,374,1670,1696]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,190,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[178,1409,190,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phaeoacremonium croatiense (HKAS 111964). a, b Appearance of ascomata on the substrate.c Cross section through ascoma. d, e Vertical section through ascomata (e with ostiolar canal). f Peridium. g Paraphyses and ascogenous hyphae with asci attached. h, i, k Ascogenous hyphae with asci attached. l, m Asci. j Paraphyses. n Germinating ascospore. o Ascospores. p, q Culture characteristic on PDA after 10 days (p = colony from above, q = colony from below). Scale bars: d, e = 50 µm, f = 20 µm, g–j, n = 10 µm, l, m, o = 5 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316494/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="68">3</figureCitation>
). To date, only the asexual morph has been reported for the species and our study provides the first sexual morph. In addition, 
<taxonomicName box="[493,827,1706,1732]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Togniniaceae" genus="Phaeoacremonium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Togniniales" pageId="9" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="croatiense">
<emphasis box="[493,827,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="68">Phaeoacremonium croatiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known in 
<collectingCountry box="[1031,1113,1706,1732]" name="Croatia" pageId="9" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Essakhi, S. &amp; Mugnai, L. &amp; Crous, P. W. &amp; Groenewald, J. Z. &amp; Surico, G." box="[1129,1348,1706,1733]" pageId="9" pageNumber="68" pagination="119 - 134" refId="ref8759" refString="Essakhi, S., Mugnai, L., Crous, P. W., Groenewald, J. Z. &amp; Surico, G. (2008) Molecular and phenotypic characterisation of novel Phaeoacremonium species isolated from esca diseased grapevines. Persoonia 21: 119 - 134. https: // doi. org / 10.3767 / 003158508 X 374385" type="journal article" year="2008">
Essakhi 
<emphasis box="[1226,1275,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="68">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
) and this is the first record for 
<collectingCountry box="[373,444,1742,1768]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="68">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
